tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul,
  transforming its generic look into a calming, professional, and sleep-themed
  interface. Additionally, a console error related to null input values was
  identified and fixed.
overview: "The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetic appeal of
  their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The
  approach involved a multi-step process: first, a detailed analysis of the
  existing styling to identify areas for improvement, followed by a
  comprehensive implementation. This included introducing a calming,
  sleep-themed color palette, redesigning the main form layout with subtle
  visual effects, enhancing all core UI components (checkboxes, radio buttons,
  sliders, progress bar, cards), and applying consistent, refined styling across
  all 14 questionnaire sections and the final report. During the review, a
  console error related to  values being passed to input components was
  identified and fixed by modifying the  component to safely convert
   to an empty string. The outcome is a visually cohesive, professional,
  and engaging application that aligns with a sleep health theme, with all
  identified bugs resolved."
